Subject: Varieties of Modern English: Davies=20

=09
-------------------------Message 1 ----------------------------------=20
Date: Mon, 19 Sep 2005 11:02:08
From: Alison Wood < Alison.Wood@pearson.com >
Subject: Varieties of Modern English: Davies=20
=20



Title: Varieties of Modern English=20
Subtitle: An Introduction=20
Series Title: Learning About Language =20

Publication Year: 2005=20
Publisher: Pearson Longman
=09   http://www.pearsoneduc.com/discipline.asp?d=3DLG
=09

Book URL: http://www.pearsoned.co.uk=20


Author: Diane Davies, University of Leicester

Paperback: ISBN: 0582369967 Pages: 184 Price: U.K. =A3 18.99


Abstract:

The English language varies in a number of ways, depending on the people
who use it, how it is used and in what circumstances.  Varieties of Modern
English gives readers the tools needed to understand the diversity of the
English language and the issues surrounding it.  The author introduces the
key terms and concepts for studying variation related to both users and
uses, as well as to illustrate and discuss particular varieties of English.=
=20

This text is suitable for undergraduate courses in varieties of English,
language variation, sociolinguistics and the history of English.=20



Linguistic Field(s): Historical Linguistics
                     Sociolinguistics

Subject Language(s): English (eng)


Written In: English  (eng)
=09
See this book announcement on our website:=20
http://linguistlist.org/get-book.html?BookID=3D14594


